********************************
***** C_HDF_READER LIBRARY *****
********************************

0 - Informations :
------------------
Version : 0.0.1
Author(s) : CGTD/UDEV/N. PASCAL
Plateform : linux

1 - Description :
-----------------
Pure C library for reading the HDF4 files

2 - Package Content :
---------------------

<installation_directory>
           |
           |-doc/
           |  |-html/    the API documentation
           |
           |-include/    the header files (*.h)
           |
           |-src/        the library sources (*.c)
           |
           |-example/    the sources of basic usage examples. See here for a quick example of main useful routines
           |             like : reading a sds data, reading an attribute, obtaining informations about an HDF file...
           |
           |-data/       an example of HDF4 file use by the example sources
           |
           |-lib/        once maked, the built library will be wrote here
           |
           |-bin/        the executables of the examples will be wrote here


3 - Prerequisites :
-------------------------
HDF4 library (>=4.2r1)

2 - Compilation :
-----------------
In the extraction directory, type :

source c_hdf_reader-compil-env.sh
make

4 - Utilisation :
-----------------
Use it as a classic libray, add :

(1) #include "c_hdf_reader.h"                        in your source files

(2) -I<include_dir> -L<lib_dir> -lc_hdf_reader       to your compiler options, where

    - <include_dir> is the directory that contains the header files (ie <installation_directory>/include)
    - <lib_dir>     is the directory that contains the library (ie <installation_directory>/lib)
